learning_outcomes.description: Explain the assumptions that underlie economic analysis and the basic principles of economics analysis such as marginal thinking.
Analyze individual consumer choice problems, including under uncertainty.

Identify the cost of production categories that are relevant for critical business decisions such as pricing, capacity abandonment, and new market entry. Develop the firms cost curves and demonstrate how they underlie the firm's supply curve. Explain how firms' decisions about prices and quantities depend on the market structure.
Analyze aggregate demand, aggregate supply, market equilibrium and welfare in market equilibrium.
Analyze deviations from the perfectly competitive market, including cases of monopoly firm behavior, asymmetric information, externalities, and public goods.
Apply basic concepts of game theory to oligopoly markets.

assessments.task_description:
Assignment 1 is comprised of problems on the content discussed in Lectures and Tutorials 1 - 6. Students may work together to solve these questions, but must submit their own work as a PDF file to blackboard. Copied solutions will be deemed as cheating and will be subject to the relevant academic misconduct procedures and penalties.

Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Translation (MT) are emerging tools that may support students in completing this assessment task. Students may appropriately use AI and/or MT in completing this assessment task. Students must clearly reference any use of AI or MT in each instance.

A failure to reference generative AI or MT use may constitute student misconduct under the Student Code of Conduct.
assessments.submission_guidelines: A PDF of a handwritten assignment must be submitted via Blackboard. Handwritten work may be completed on paper and then scanned or photographed, or created digitally using a tablet and stylus. Submissions that are not handwritten will incur a penalty of 15% of the maximum possible mark for the assessment item.
assessments.deferral_or_extension: You may be able to apply for an extension.
assessments.late_submission: A penalty of 10% of the maximum possible mark will be deducted per 24 hours from time submission is due for up to 7 days. After 7 days, you will receive a mark of 0.
assessments.additional_info: You may be able to apply for an extension.
